agerly anticipate the holy month of Ramadan as they seek divine blessings with both young and old fasting from sunrise to sunset for the month. At the end of the month,Â Muslims celebrate Eid ul-Fitr, which is a time of merriment and joy, spent with loved ones. The management and staff of Tabloid Newspapers would like to wish all Muslim advertisers and readers Ramadan Mubarak. As you fast and offer prayers to God, may you find your peace and happiness.